<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FF82F933FE28FE246461FE13" author="Philippi" box="[388,532,452,474]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Philippi, R. A. (1844) Enumeratio molluscorum Siciliae cum viventium tum in tellure tertiaria fossilium, quae in itinere suo observavit. Eduard Anton, Halle, IV + 303 pp." type="book" year="1844">Philippi, 1844</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
—Melone &amp; Taviani 1984 (p. 152, figs. 1–10); 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FF82F933FBA5FE2562B8FE13" author="Repetto" box="[1033,1229,452,474]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Repetto, G., Orlando, F. &amp; Arduino, G. (2005) Conchiglie del Mediterraneo: 1770 specie illustrate con distribuzione e frequenza. Amici del Museo &quot; Federico Eusebio &quot;, Alba, 392 pp." type="book" year="2005">
Repetto 
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FBF3FE2562E6FE13" box="[1119,1171,452,474]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
(p. 224, bottom left fig.); 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FF82F933FF53FE0367D9FE31" author="Penas" box="[255,428,482,504]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Penas, A., Rolan, E., Luque, A. A., Templado, J., Moreno, D., Rubio, F., Salas, C., Sierra, A. &amp; Gofas, S. (2006) Moluscos marinos de la isla de Alboran. Iberus, 24 (1), 23 - 151." type="journal article" year="2006">
Peñas 
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FEECFE036701FE31" box="[320,372,482,504]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
(p. 128, figs. 282–284); Mastrototaro 
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FC9DFE036511FE31" box="[817,868,482,504]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2010 (fig. 5 b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF82F933FF3BFDC56719FD07" blockId="70.[151,1437,549,970]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FF3BFDC567EEFDF7" bold="true" box="[151,411,549,574]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Low conical, almost discoidal shell; very low spire; rounded aperture with weak adaxial and abaxial angulation; deep and wide umbilicus bordered by 2 rows of elongated knobs; robust peripheral keel; spiral rows of squarish nodes ceasing on the mid-base; dense axial striation on base. Protoconch: heterostrophic; about 2 whorls, the first immersed; diameter about 680 µm; surface smooth; transition to the teleoconch marked by a thread-like varix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3766538FF82F933FF6BFD396681FCDC" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF82F933FF6BFD396681FCDC" blockId="70.[151,1437,549,970]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FF6BFD396726FD3B" bold="true" box="[199,339,729,754]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC67 (2 specimens), BC70 (1), BC71 (2), BC72 (17). Maximum diameter: 
<quantity id="4C949B56FF82F933FF3BFD1D6685FCDC" box="[151,240,765,790]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3766538FF82F933FF6BFCC16259FC03" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF82F933FF6BFCC16556FC6F" blockId="70.[151,1437,549,970]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FF6BFCC1679FFCF3" bold="true" box="[199,490,801,826]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FF82F933FE5BFCC26499FCF3" authority="Marwick, 1931" authorityName="Marwick" authorityYear="1931" box="[503,748,801,826]" class="Gastropoda" family="Architectonicidae" genus="Discotectonica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FE5BFCC26499FCF3" box="[503,748,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Discotectonica discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed from the Lusitanic province to West Africa and the Mediterranean, as well as in the Caribbean area; it is a rare species dwelling on circalittoral to bathyal mud (Melone &amp; Taviani 1984; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B42FF82F933FE11FC8A64D1FC4B" author="Poppe" box="[445,676,874,898]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" refString="Poppe, G. T. &amp; Goto, Y. (1991) European Seashells. Volume I. (Polyplacophora, Caudofoveata, Solenogastra, Gastropoda). Verlag Christa Hemmen, Wiesbaden, 352 pp." type="book" year="1991">
Poppe &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="49A8F851FF82F933FD84FC8A6415FC4B" box="[552,608,874,898]" country="Malta" name="Zebbug" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Goto</collectingRegion>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Santa Maria di Leuca 
<collectionCode id="ED7DAE76FF82F933FC56FC8A624FFC4B" box="[1018,1082,874,898]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15029" name="Central Wyoming College" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">CWC</collectionCode>
biotope, it was found on living colonies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D30FF82F933FEB5FC6D656AFC6F" authority="Mastrototaro et al. 2010" authorityName="Mastrototaro et al." authorityYear="2010" box="[281,799,909,934]" class="Anthozoa" family="Oculinidae" genus="Madrepora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scleractinia" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="oculata">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FEB5FC6D6786FC6F" box="[281,499,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Madrepora oculata</emphasis>
(Mastrototaro 
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FD37FC6E64A6FC6F" box="[667,723,909,934]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">et al.</emphasis>
2010)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD336B3FF82F933FF6BFC516259FC03" blockId="70.[151,1437,549,970]" box="[199,1068,945,970]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="B918EAA1FF82F933FF6BFC51671DFC03" bold="true" box="[199,360,945,970]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fossil record.</emphasis>
Pleistocene of Ischia, southern Italy (Melone &amp; Taviani 1984).
</paragraph>
